hotspot.title: About
hotspot.description: First time I ever held a hook was as a little girl, I cheerfully made lots of cute tiny purses and bags for friends, and even sold a few. However, I didn't continue to crochet - not till I became an architect, a graphics designer, and a full time freelance animator. I recently picked up crocheting again, and I was "hooked" to say the least. Then came in the soft skills and discipline I had developed from other parts of my life, that have continued to have a positive impact on my productivity and how I deliver these special crochet and more to you.

I am a Digital Artist/Illustrator, redefining the black culture/community through my dynamic style. I love being dynamic when illustrating and designing. I create visual works/ designs for brands that capture the aesthetics of Black, African culture.
